It's got potential, but you need to elaborate a whole lot more. Under what circumstances were it's properties brought to the attention of the Foundation? Could it be used to nullify the powers of SCP-239? If it induces physical silence, could it also silence their thoughts to telepathic SCPs?

Also, it is a bit… tame by general SCP standards - try, say, having victims silenced for much longer - perhaps permanently - or their tongues burnt out unless certain precautions are taken.

The main problem, though, is definitely length. Pad it out a bit, maybe see if you can find a good image.





